# Node.js Microservices Practice Project

This project demonstrates a **basic microservices architecture** using **Node.js and Express.js**.
Each service runs independently on a **different port** and can be started in **separate terminals**.

The project was developed as part of **backend practice tasks during internship training**.

---

# 📂 Project Structure

```
node-microservices-tasks
│
├── student-service
│     └── server.js
│
├── course-service
│     └── server.js
│
├── college-service
│     └── server.js
│
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

Each folder represents a **separate microservice**.

---

# 🚀 Services Overview

| Service         | Port | Description                     |
| --------------- | ---- | ------------------------------- |
| Student Service | 3001 | Handles student CRUD operations |
| Course Service  | 3002 | Manages course data             |
| College Service | 3003 | Manages college data            |

Each service runs **independently** and exposes its own API endpoints.

---

# 🧑‍🎓 Student Service

Base URL:

```
http://localhost:3001
```

Endpoints:

| Method | Endpoint      | Description       |
| ------ | ------------- | ----------------- |
| GET    | /students     | Get all students  |
| GET    | /students/:id | Get student by ID |
| POST   | /students     | Add new student   |

Example Student Object:

```
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Rahul",
  "age": 20
}
```

---

# 📚 Course Service

Base URL:

```
http://localhost:3002
```

Endpoints:

| Method | Endpoint | Description     |
| ------ | -------- | --------------- |
| GET    | /courses | Get all courses |
| POST   | /courses | Add new course  |

Example Course Object:

```
{
  "id": 1,
  "title": "Node.js"
}
```

---

# 🏫 College Service

Base URL:

```
http://localhost:3003
```

Endpoints:

| Method | Endpoint  | Description      |
| ------ | --------- | ---------------- |
| GET    | /colleges | Get all colleges |
| POST   | /colleges | Add new college  |

Example College Object:

```
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "MIT Mysore"
}
```

---

# ⚙️ Installation

Clone the repository:

```
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/node-microservices-tasks.git
```

Move into the project folder:

```
cd node-microservices-tasks
```

Install dependencies:

```
npm install express
```

---

# ▶️ Running the Services

Open **three terminals** and run each service separately.

### Terminal 1 – Student Service

```
cd student-service
node server.js
```

Runs on:

```
http://localhost:3001
```

---

### Terminal 2 – Course Service

```
cd course-service
node server.js
```

Runs on:

```
http://localhost:3002
```

---

### Terminal 3 – College Service

```
cd college-service
node server.js
```

Runs on:

```
http://localhost:3003
```

---

# 🧪 API Testing

All APIs were tested using **Postman** to verify request and response behavior.

Example request:

```
GET http://localhost:3001/students
```

